## 6. Candidate claim areas for legal assessment

The following are not formal claims, but candidate areas for patent attorney analysis.

### A. Computer-implemented method
A method for coordinating one or more language-model-based components through role-bounded processing cycles, structured state handoffs, mismatch evaluation, and feedback-sensitive state revision.

### B. System architecture
A system comprising distinct functional layers for structural mapping, continuation comparison/revision, and symbolic contextual interpretation, operating over a shared structured state.

### C. State update mechanism
A structured state grammar that preserves event trains, role outputs, mismatch history, recovery state, and contextual framing across cycles.

### D. Mismatch and recovery mechanism
A method for comparing predicted continuation with returned trace structure and updating future processing through bounded correction, residual tracking, recovery, and recontact handling.

### E. Conformance / failure taxonomy
A method for evaluating whether a role-separated AI coordination system remains within protocol bounds, including detection of role fusion, semantic contamination, false continuity, false recovery, and coherence loss.

### F. Technical deployments
Specific implementations in robotics, imaging, engineering constraint reasoning, enterprise assistants, or device-level personal assistants where technical effects can be measured.

